universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : Unique among consoles, the Vectrex came with its own built-in vector monitor — it drew crisp glowing lines directly, not a grid of pixels, so it never needed a TV. A Motorola 6809 steered the beam through a DAC, and plastic overlays added colour to the black-and-white screen.
